 grand maximum of\nactivity in the second half of the 20th century. The uniqueness of the grand\nmaximum is confirmed for the last 250 years. It is shown that the adoption of a\nlinear relationship between the data of Wolf and Wolfer results in grossly\ninflated group numbers in the 18th and 19th centuries in some reconstructions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 20 Dec 2015 19:30:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-02-03"}
