c state, and\neven the superconducting state can be realized in $1T$-TaS$_{2}$, which makes\nthe novel material have very promising applications in the future electronic\ndevices.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 21 Dec 2015 09:58:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 24 Jun 2016 16:58:15 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 2 Sep 2016 16:22:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-09-15"}
